---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="DNS Monitoring for IT Teams — DNSSnuff"
  description="Monitor your domain estate. Get alerted the moment anything changes. DNSSnuff Pro runs daily DNS health checks and alerts you before users notice."
  currentPath="/use-cases/it-teams"
>
  <Nav slot="nav" />

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">For IT Teams</div>
      <h1>Know about it before your users do.</h1>
      <p>DNSSnuff Pro monitors your domain estate daily, alerts you the moment anything changes, and keeps a full history of every check. DNS problems don't have to become incidents.</p>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="/auth/sign-up" class="btn btn-primary">Start Free Trial →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2>DNS problems don't announce themselves.</h2>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;margin-top:1.5rem">
        <p>A certificate expires. A blacklist listing appears. Someone updates an SPF record and pushes it to the wrong zone. A nameserver change propagates incorrectly to part of the network.</p>
        <p>None of these send you an email. None of them show up in your monitoring dashboard. They show up in a support ticket three days later, or in a call from a senior manager asking why emails stopped arriving.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="background:var(--bg-2);border-top:1px solid var(--border);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:2.5rem">What DNSSnuff watches for you</h2>
      <div class="grid-2">
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Daily health checks across all domains</h4>
          <p>Every domain in your dashboard is checked every 24 hours — automatically. No manual intervention, no scripts to maintain.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Instant change alerts</h4>
          <p>The moment any check result changes on any domain, you get an email notification. Not a weekly digest. Not a dashboard you have to remember to look at. An alert, immediately, when something changes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Certificate expiry tracking</h4>
          <p>DNSSnuff tracks SSL certificate expiry on all monitored domains and alerts you well in advance. No more emergency renewals at 2am.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Blacklist monitoring</h4>
          <p>Your domain and mail server IPs are checked against 50+ real-time block lists every day. If anything gets listed, you'll know within 24 hours — not three weeks later when someone complains their emails aren't arriving.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>DMARC and SPF change detection</h4>
          <p>Someone updated an SPF record and forgot to tell you. An email marketing platform added itself to your SPF without authorisation. DNSSnuff catches both.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Historical tracking</h4>
          <p>Every check is stored. When something breaks, you can see exactly when it changed. Correlate a delivery issue with a DNS update from last Tuesday. Know what changed, and when.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid-2" style="align-items:start">
        <div>
          <h2>Multi-domain dashboard</h2>
          <p style="margin:1rem 0">Manage your entire domain estate from one view. Health scores across all monitored domains at a glance. Drill into any domain for the full 72-check report. Filter by issue severity.</p>
          <h4 style="margin-top:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;color:var(--text)">Ideal for:</h4>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Internal domain estate (primary, subdomains, regional domains)</li>
            <li>Subsidiary or brand domains</li>
            <li>Partner domains you're responsible for</li>
            <li>Pre-production and staging environments</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:1rem">Plain-English results</h3>
          <p>You don't need to be a DNS expert to use DNSSnuff — and neither does the person you're reporting to.</p>
          <p style="margin-top:1rem">Every failed check includes a specific explanation of what's wrong, why it matters, and what to do about it. Share a report link with a developer, a vendor, or a manager without them needing to decode RFC notation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="text-center" style="background:var(--bg-2);border-top:1px solid var(--border)">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Put your domain estate under automated watch.</h2>
      <p style="margin:1rem auto 2rem;max-width:480px">No card required to start. Cancel any time.</p>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="/auth/sign-up" class="btn btn-primary">Start Free Trial →</a>
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-outline">Run a Free Report First →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Layout>
